Similar interpretations are true for any number of vectors spanning an formula_94-dimensional parallelotope; the exterior product of vectors formula_396, that is formula_397, has a magnitude equal to the volume of the formula_94-parallelotope. An formula_94-vector does not necessarily have a shape of a parallelotope – this is a convenient visualization. It could be any shape, although the volume equals that of the parallelotope.
